Alan Wake 2 is a sequel to a cult classic horror game, in which the player takes control of Alan Wake, a writer, who becomes entrapped inside the world of his own novel. During the first game, Alan managed to save his wife Alice, at the expense of stranding himself at Cauldron Lake. The plot of the sequel continues 13 years after. Detective Saga Anderson and her partner Alex Casey come to the town of Bright Hills, where, allegedly, “The Cult of the Tree” resides. Rumor has it that its members are lunatics, who wear deer masks, walk around the town and search for people who are in any way related to Alan’s stories. The unlucky ones to stumble upon the cultists would have their hearts cut out. If you are wondering how the novelist’s story will play out, what role does Saga have to play and how the cult is involved in it, then we offer you to buy Alan Wake 2 CD key and find out for yourself. Sam Lake returns to the sequel as a writer and a director. He’s the one who created the story and characters of the first Alan Wake, Max Payne, Quantum Break and Control. Expend something grand from this entry as well!

Visually and gameplay-wise this game is similar to such titles as Resident Evil 4 (2023) and Silent Hill: Downpour. Dark and gloomy areas, hiding unimaginable horrors in thick mist, while the same horrors will come to you directly in the forest. A depressing atmosphere of small towns with odd habitants. Mysteries, monsters, jumpscares and traversing dimly-lit places with a flashlight – all the beloved staples of the genre are here! If you like the survivor-horror genre with fantastic graphics and movie-quality cinematics, then you definitely should buy Alan Wake 2 CD key.

You’ll have to get through the cultists, wild animals and other weird creatures from the shadow realm. Even though you will be equipped with a flashlight to light your way and blind your foes, as well as a handgun to deal damage, the ammunition will be scarce and flashlight batteries will run out sooner or later. Rationing your resources is key if you don’t want to struggle with monsters in total darkness.
